HOUSE RESOLUTION 162
By Vaughan
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Harlan Paul
Whitehorn on becoming an Eagle Scout.
WHEREAS, at a time when this nation's youth face difficult challenges, the Boy Scouts
of America is one of our finest assets, providing young people with an educational program that
contributes significantly to their character development, citizenship training, and improved
mental and physical fitness; and
WHEREAS, the highest rank a Scout can attain in the Boy Scouts of America Scouts
BSA program is that of Eagle Scout, and Harlan Paul Whitehorn, after considerable effort and
diligent preparation, has joined the prestigious Eagle Court of Honor; and
WHEREAS, his notable record of achievement with Boy Scout Troop 331 includes
numerous merit badges and distinguished service; and
WHEREAS, demonstrating consistent leadership among his peers, Mr. Whitehorn
helped five fellow Scouts complete their Eagle projects, served as Assistant Senior Patrol
Leader for two years, and served as Crew Leader for two fifty-mile backpacking treks at
Philmont Scout Ranch; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Whitehorn's Eagle project greatly contributed to the betterment of his
community and reflected the true spirit of volunteerism; and
WHEREAS, outside of Scouting, Harlan Whitehorn is extremely involved in community
service; through Leadership Collierville, he volunteered with Adopt-a-Highway to clean up three
miles of public road, helped wrap and pack donation boxes for the homeless and elderly in his
community, and helped set up a trivia night fundraiser; and
HR0162
013580
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Mr. Whitehorn is also a member of Field of Friends, which hosts baseball
and kickball games for students with special needs, and Mission 1:8 Day, which is a school-
sponsored day of service in the Memphis community; and
WHEREAS, Harlan Whitehorn has volunteered in numerous other capacities, including
dressing up as the Easter Bunny for the Rockin Rabbit event, collecting school supplies and
packing backpacks for students in need, organizing and delivering food for families in need,
volunteering at the Scare on the Square Halloween event, and volunteering with the Forever
Young Veterans and Alpha Omega Veterans Services; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Whitehorn has received the Joseph A. Clayton Award in all four years of
high school for exceptional grades and is a Top 20 Student in the Briarcrest Christian High
School Class of 2026; he also plays for the varsity bowling and tennis teams and received the
Joe Rowell Heart of a Saint Award for bowling; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Whitehorn is involved in numerous extracurriculars at Briarcrest
Christian School, including National Honor Society, Key Club, Latin Club, German Club,
National Latin Honor Society, and Film Club; and
WHEREAS, a young man of deep faith, Harlan Whitehorn is highly involved in his
church's youth group and serves as a Vacation Bible School leader and a Sunday School
helper; and
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that we should recognize Mr. Whitehorn as one of the most
outstanding young people in our State; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and
congratulate Harlan Paul Whitehorn on becoming an Eagle Scout and extend to him our best
wishes for every future success.
- 2 - 013580

BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
